<p style="Heading 3" xid="2880">Lab</p>
<p style="Normal" xid="2881">The objectives of this lab is to use the shell commands we learned in this chapter and understand their proper usage patterns. The outcome will be that you will be able to successfully use the Linux Shell for navigation, file creation, and file modification. Resist the temptation to use the GUI file manger and a web browser. All actions will be done through the shell.</p>
<p level="4" listid="1071" parentid="1061" xid="2882" props="font-family:Times New Roman; dom-dir:ltr; default-tab-interval:0.4925in; margin-left:3.175000cm; lang:en-US; text-indent:-0.635000cm; list-style:Lower Roman List; margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in; font-size:12pt; field-font:NULL"><field type="list_label" xid="2883"></field>	Navigate from your home directory to your Downloads directory</p>
<p level="5" listid="1072" parentid="1071" xid="2884" props="font-family:Times New Roman; dom-dir:ltr; default-tab-interval:0.4925in; margin-left:3.810000cm; lang:en-US; text-indent:-0.635000cm; margin-bottom:0in; margin-top:0in; list-style:Lower Roman List; font-size:12pt; field-font:NULL"><field type="list_label" xid="2885"></field>	Take a screenshot of the output of the <c props="font-family:Courier New">ls</c> command. Name the file lastname-firstname-screenshot-week-5-ls.(jpg or png)</p>
