<p style="Normal" xid="3476"><c props="font-weight:bold">Outcomes</c></p>
<p style="Text body" xid="3477">At the conclusion of this chapter you will be able to install packages and manage dependecies through using standard package managers dnf, yum, and apt. You will also be comfortable compiling software from source using a tar ball and python setup tools.</p>
<p style="Heading 2" xid="3478">Package Managers</p>
<p level="3" listid="1338" parentid="1327" xid="3479" props="font-family:Times New Roman; dom-dir:ltr; default-tab-interval:0.4925in; margin-left:2.540000cm; lang:en-US; text-indent:-0.635000cm; list-style:Bullet List; margin-top:0in; margin-bottom:0in; font-size:12pt; field-font:NULL"><field type="list_label" xid="3480"></field>	yum</p>
